## Three-Point Anti-Goal Evaluation

Admissibility before acting: the orchestrator screens every move against all three tripwires before dispatch. Reading or using a fixture without a content hash is vetoed. Writing `tasks/okra-governed-loop.md` directly is vetoed. Reporting acceptance without deterministic evidence is vetoed. If a cost is unclear, the orchestrator uses a dry-run/propose-cost worker before admitting a committing move.

Direct read after acting: after a content read, write, status generation, or verify action, the orchestrator reads `.okra/checkins.jsonl`, `.okra/ledger.jsonl`, worker progress logs, and helper output directly. It does not accept worker self-report as proof.

Paired with objective progress: `governed_content_use_rate >= 0.90` only counts as success while all three anti-goal metrics remain at zero. A high governed-use rate with missing write evidence or single-narrative acceptance is not a win; it opens `breaking`.

## Operating Loop

Cadence:

| Moment | Orchestrator action |
| --- | --- |
| Start of turn | Verify store, read current frame/tree, inspect open flags, and check metric freshness. |
| Pre-dispatch | Run admissibility against `ungoverned_direct_read_count`, `ungoverned_direct_write_count`, and `single_llm_truth_acceptance_count`. |
| Worker heartbeat | Require DKR/PKR worker progress reports on completion, unknown discovery, flag-worthy risk, and every ten minutes for long-running workers. |
| Post-move | Append direct objective and anti-goal metric reads to `ledger.jsonl`. |
| End of turn | Append a steering check-in, generate `.okra/status.md` from source records, verify the store, and set `next_check_at`. |

