## PKR Progress Signals

Every PKR check-in reports: off-track work, quality drift, churn, late discovery, stale metrics, and scope or authority concerns. The current steering check-in reports all signals false for `pkr-1`, `pkr-2`, and `pkr-3`. If a progression worker hits an unknown, it hands back to the orchestrator; the orchestrator decides whether to fund another DKR.

## Flags and Lifecycle

| Flag | Opens when | Blocking behavior | Lifecycle |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `cannot` | Discovery budget is exhausted, learning flatlines, or storage friction prevents OKRA work. | Stops the affected DKR or branch. | `open -> acknowledged -> resolved` when budget/scope/tooling is fixed, or `waived` by the human. |
| `breaking` | Any tripwire crosses: missing source read record, missing final write record, store verification failure, or single-narrative acceptance. | Pauses committing moves by default. | `open -> acknowledged -> resolved` after deterministic evidence is appended, or `waived` by the human for a specific move. |
| `pointless` | CKR/PKR work finishes or CKR metric moves but objective stays flat after the lag window. | Stops the affected branch and forces re-aim. | `open -> acknowledged -> resolved` after the human changes scope/targeting or evidence shows objective movement, or `waived` by the human. |
| `authority_drift` | The loop or a worker changes the frame, relaxes a threshold, expands scope, bypasses approval, contacts a human directly, or writes outside the action envelope. | Stops the proposed move and escalates to the human. | `open -> acknowledged -> resolved` only inside recorded human resolution, or `waived` by the human. |

